<inglise> 2. 'joint account' shall mean an account opened in the names of two or more persons or over which two or more persons have rights that may operate against the signature of one or more of those persons; </inglise>
<eesti> 2) &uuml;hiskonto - konto, mis on avatud v&auml;hemalt kahe isiku nimel v&otilde;i millele v&auml;hemalt kahel isikul on &otilde;igusi, mida v&otilde;idakse kasutada &uuml;he v&otilde;i mitme sellise isiku allkirjaga; </eesti>
<inglise> 3. 'unavailable deposit' shall mean a deposit that is due and payable but has not been paid by a credit institution under the legal and contractual conditions applicable thereto, where either: </inglise>
<eesti> 3) peatatud hoius - hoius, mille makset&auml;htp&auml;ev on saabunud ja mis kuulub maksmisele, kuid mida krediidiasutus ei ole maksnud tema suhtes kohaldatavate juriidiliste ja lepinguliste tingimuste kohaselt, kui: </eesti>
<inglise> (i) the relevant competent authorities have determined that in their view the credit institution concerned appears to be unable for the time being, for reasons which are directly related to its financial circumstances, to repay the deposit and to have no current prospect of being able to do so. </inglise>
<eesti> i) asjaomased p&auml;devad asutused on otsustanud, et nende arvates ei suuda k&otilde;nealune krediidiasutus otseselt tema rahalise olukorraga seotud p&otilde;hjustel hoiuseid hetkel tagasi maksta ega suuda seda ilmselt l&auml;hitulevikuski teha. </eesti>
<inglise> The competent authorities shall make that determination as soon as possible and at the latest 21 days after first becoming satisfied that a credit institution has failed to repay deposits which are due and payable; or (ii) a judicial authority has made a ruling for reasons which are directly related to the credit institution's financial circumstances which has the effect of suspending depositors' ability to make claims against it, should that occur before the aforementioned determination has been made; </inglise>
<eesti> P&auml;devad asutused teevad selle otsuse niipea kui v&otilde;imalik ja hiljemalt 21 p&auml;eva p&auml;rast esmakordset veendumist, et krediidiasutus ei ole tagasi maksnud hoiuseid, mille makset&auml;htp&auml;ev on saabunud ja mis kuuluvad maksmisele; v&otilde;i ii) kohtuorgan on otseselt krediidiasutuse rahalise olukorraga seotud p&otilde;hjustel teinud otsuse, mille tagaj&auml;rjel ei saa hoiustajad esitada n&otilde;udeid krediidiasutuse vastu, kui selline otsus tehakse enne eespool nimetatud otsust; </eesti>
<inglise> 4. 'credit institution' shall mean an undertaking the business of which is to receive deposits or other repayable funds from the public and to grant credits for its own account; </inglise>
<eesti> 4) krediidiasutus - ettev&otilde;tja, kelle tegevuseks on hoiuste v&otilde;i muude tagasimakstavate vahendite vastuv&otilde;tmine &uuml;ldsuselt ja laenu andmine oma huvides; </eesti>
<inglise> 5. 'branch' shall mean a place of business which forms a legally dependent part of a credit institution and which conducts directly all or some of the operations inherent in the business of credit institutions; any number of branches set up in the same Member State by a credit institution which has its head office in another Member State shall be regarded as a single branch. </inglise>
<eesti> 5) filiaal - tegevuskoht, mis on krediidiasutuse juriidiliselt s&otilde;ltuv osa ja kus tehakse otseselt k&otilde;iki v&otilde;i m&otilde;ningaid krediidiasutuste tegevusele omaseid tehinguid; k&otilde;iki filiaale, mille on &uuml;hes liikmesriigis asutanud teises liikmesriigis asuva peakontoriga krediidiasutus, k&auml;sitletakse &uuml;he filiaalina. </eesti>
