<inglise> ANNEX II </inglise>
<eesti> II LISA </eesti>
<inglise> Guiding principles </inglise>
<eesti> Juhtp&otilde;him&otilde;tted </eesti>
<inglise> Where a branch applies to join a host Member State scheme for supplementary cover, the host Member State scheme will bilaterally establish with the home Member State scheme appropriate rules and procedures for paying compensation to depositors at that branch. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui filiaal taotleb vastuv&otilde;tva liikmesriigi skeemiga liitumist t&auml;iendava kaitse saamiseks, kehtestab vastuv&otilde;tva liikmesriigi skeem kahepoolselt koos p&auml;ritoluliikmesriigi skeemiga asjakohased eeskirjad selle filiaali hoiustajatele h&uuml;vitise maksmiseks ja maksmise korra. </eesti>
<inglise> The following principles shall apply both to the drawing up of those procedures and in the framing of the membership conditions applicable to such a branch (as referred to in Article 4 (2)): </inglise>
<eesti> Nii selle korra kui ka k&otilde;nealusele filiaalile kohaldatavate liitumistingimuste (nimetatud artikli 4 l&otilde;ikes 2) koostamisel kohaldatakse j&auml;rgmiseid p&otilde;him&otilde;tteid: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) the host Member State scheme will retain full rights to impose its objective and generally applied rules on participating credit institutions; it will be able to require the provision of relevant information and have the right to verify such information with the home Member State's competent authorities; </inglise>
<eesti> a) vastuv&otilde;tva liikmesriigi skeemile j&auml;&auml;vad t&auml;ielikud &otilde;igused kehtestada osalevate krediidiasutuste suhtes oma erapooletuid ja &uuml;ldkohaldatavaid eeskirju; ta v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda asjakohase teabe esitamist ja tal on &otilde;igus kontrollida seda teavet p&auml;ritoluliikmesriigi p&auml;devates asutustes; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) the host Member State scheme will meet claims for supplementary compensation upon a declaration from the home Member State's competent authorities that deposits are unavailable. </inglise>
<eesti> b) vastuv&otilde;tva liikmesriigi skeem rahuldab t&auml;iendava h&uuml;vitisega seotud n&otilde;uded p&auml;rast seda, kui p&auml;ritoluliikmesriigi p&auml;devad asutused on talle teatanud hoiuste peatamisest. </eesti>
<inglise> The host Member State scheme will retain full rights to verify a depositor's entitlement according to its own standards and procedures before paying supplementary compensation; </inglise>
<eesti> Vastuv&otilde;tva liikmesriigi skeemile j&auml;&auml;vad t&auml;ielikud &otilde;igused kontrollida hoiustaja &otilde;igusi oma normide ja korra kohaselt enne t&auml;iendava h&uuml;vitise maksmist; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) home Member State and host Member State schemes will cooperate fully with each other to ensure that depositors receive compensation promptly and in the correct amounts. </inglise>
<eesti> c) p&auml;ritoluliikmesriigi ja vastuv&otilde;tva liikmesriigi skeemid teevad teineteisega igak&uuml;lgset koost&ouml;&ouml;d tagamaks, et hoiustajad saavad h&uuml;vitist viivitamata ja &otilde;iges summas. </eesti>
<inglise> In particular, they will agree on how the existence of a counterclaim which may give rise to set-off under either scheme will affect the compensation paid to the depositor by each scheme; </inglise>
<eesti> Eelk&otilde;ige lepivad nad kokku, kuidas emma-kumma skeemi raames tasaarvestust p&otilde;hjustada v&otilde;iv vastun&otilde;ue m&otilde;jutab h&uuml;vitist, mida kumbki skeem hoiustajale maksab; </eesti>
<inglise> (d) host Member State schemes will be entitled to charge branches for supplementary cover on an appropriate basis which takes into account the guarantee funded by the home Member State scheme. </inglise>
<eesti> d) vastuv&otilde;tva liikmesriigi skeemil on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda filiaalidelt t&auml;iendava kaitse eest p&otilde;hjendatud tasu, v&otilde;ttes arvesse p&auml;ritoluliikmesriigi skeemi rahastatavat tagatist. </eesti>
<inglise> To facilitate charging, the host Member State scheme will be entitled to assume that its liability will in all circumstances be limited to the excess of the guarantee it has offered over the guarantee offered by the home Member State regardless of whether the home Member State actually pays any compensation in respect of deposits held within the host Member State's territory. </inglise>
<eesti> Tasu sissen&otilde;udmise h&otilde;lbustamiseks on vastuv&otilde;tva liikmesriigi skeemil &otilde;igus eeldada, et tema vastutus piirdub igal juhul tema pakutava tagatise ja p&auml;ritoluliikmesriigi pakutava tagatise vahega, olenemata sellest, kas p&auml;ritoluliikmesriik maksab h&uuml;vitist vastuv&otilde;tva liikmesriigi territooriumil olevate hoiuste suhtes. </eesti>
